"{\"abstract\":\"Existing scene flow approaches mainly focus on two-frame stereo-pair configurations and reconstruct an image-based representation of scene flow. Instead, we propose a variational formulation of scene flow relative to a coarse proxy geometry, which is better suited for many views. Furthermore, a linear basis is used to represent temporal surface flow, allowing for longer-range temporal correspondence with fewer variables. Our formulation takes known proxy motion into account (e.g, if the proxy is a tracked human subject), which enables 3D trajectory reconstruction when only a single view is available. Additionally, through the appropriate proxy and basis, our framework generalizes existing approaches for scene flow, optic-flow, and two-frame stereo. We illustrate results on real-data for both static and moving proxy surfaces over several frames.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2959338\",\"name\":\"N. Birkbeck\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2959338\"},{\"authorId\":\"2505506\",\"name\":\"D. Cobzas\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2505506\"},{\"authorId\":\"3160299\",\"name\":\"Martin J\\u00e4gersand\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/3160299\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2627132\",\"name\":\"Degui Xiao\"},{\"authorId\":\"2499651\",\"name\":\"Qiuwei Yang\"},{\"authorId\":\"40108647\",\"name\":\"B. Yang\"},{\"authorId\":\"47748186\",\"name\":\"Wei Wei\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1007/s11042-015-3091-6\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"1f485e5d64f078a97bae33a980cc25c1151c74e1\",\"title\":\"Monocular scene flow estimation via variational method\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/1f485e5d64f078a97bae33a980cc25c1151c74e1\",\"venue\":\"Multimedia Tools and Applications\",\"year\":2015},{\"arxivId\":\"1803.10193\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3407706\",\"name\":\"Vladislav Golyanik\"},{\"authorI